A BOY of 15 forced his way past security and rapped for Nasty C. And the hip pop star was so impressed, he let Lucas Malong perform with him! A source close to Nasty C said: &ldquo;Lucas and his manager, Junior Lavie, forced their way in to meet Nasty C for five minutes. But they stayed for 20, and the boy&rsquo;s talent made Nasty C cry!&rdquo;Another source said: &ldquo;Lucas has been eager to share a song with Nasty C. The boy looks up to Nasty C, as he inspires him to make it in the music industry.&rdquo;Sunday Sun has learnt that Nasty C met Lucas during his performance at Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban recentlylast weekend .The SunTeam contacted Lucas through Junior and he said: &ldquo;Nasty C is my idol, he inspires me to stay in the game.&ldquo;When I heard about his background and how he started in the music industry, I told myself I won&rsquo;t give up.&rdquo;For his part, Nasty C said: &ldquo;The boy is currently trending after he shared the stage with me. This boy is good! He has my blessings.&ldquo;In fact, he&rsquo;s just a blessing!&rdquo;